    Database

    Database.Role
    List of Roles corresponding to roles defined for a certain MariaDB server and Przychodnia database
    Lekarz
    It represents a physician corresponding to the one stored in the table Lekarze of the database.

    Class for a window which opens before login and enables setting connection parameters

    NowyPacjentWindow
    This class is responsible for a window which enables a user to add new patients.
    Pacjent
    Represents a patient - an entity stored in the Przychodnia database.
    Pomieszczenie
    Represents a room where an appointment takes place, references this entity stored in Przychodnia database.
    PrzegladajWizyteWindow
    This class is responsible for a window which enables finding details of a particular appointment and editing them, if possible.
    PrzychodniaCrusher
    The Przychodnia Crusher program is a client application for a database server, with which it forms the complete system of data storage for a small medical clinic.
    RealizujWizyteWindow
    Responsible for a window which enables realization of appointments by physicians.
    SaveableToPrzychodnia
    The interface that should be implemented by any object that is going to be saved in the Przychodnia database.
    Searching
    A class which should be inherited by any object that is going to be searched for in the Przychodnia database.
    UpdateLekarzeWindow

    UpdatePacjentWindow

    User
    Represents a user logged in to a database.
    WindowHandler
    Responsible for closing the application with a preceding prompt.
    Wizyta
    A class that represents an appointment in a clinic, as stored in the Przychodnia database.
    WyszukajLekarzaWindow

    WyszukajPacjentaWindow
    Responsible for a window which enables searching for a patient in a database.
    WyszukajPomieszczenieWindow
    Responsible for window which enables the user to look for rooms in the database.
    WyszukajWizytaWindow
    Responsible for window which enables to search for appointments in the database.
